!*HYDROPONIC NUTRIENT UPTAKE PARAMETERS (SILBERBUSH 2005 BASELINE)
  0.841  29.400 0.668  31.680 20.0  20.0 10.0    JMAX_NO3, KM_NO3, JMAX_NH4, KM_NH4, KI_NO3, KI_NH4, KI_TIN (mg/cm/d, mg/L)
! Unit conversion: Vmax[nmol/cm/s]*MW[g/mol]*1000*86400*1e-9 = mg/cm/d
!   NO3-N: 13.9 nmol/cm/s = 16.82 mg N/cm/d; HATS Km=0.21 mmol/L = 2.94 mg N/L
!   NH4-N: 18.4 nmol/cm/s = 22.27 mg N/cm/d; HATS Km=0.75 mmol/L = 10.56 mg N/L
!   Ki values activate optional Haldane inhibition at high concentration.
!   Ki_TIN adds shared inhibition from total inorganic N (NO3+NH4).
!   NO3 inhibition is weak (Ki=200 mg/L); NH4 inhibition is stronger (Ki=40 mg/L).
! NH4 toxicity stress: NTOXS = 1/(1+(NH4_SOL/NH4_TOX_K)^NH4_TOX_N)
!   NH4_TOX_K: NH4 concentration (mg/L) at which NTOXS=0.5 (half-inhibition)
!   NH4_TOX_N: Hill coefficient (steepness); n=2 gives smooth sigmoidal response
!   Calibrated: K=138, n=2.0 -> SIM TRT6/TRT5=0.418 (OBS=0.421, Sharkey 2024)
!   Note: NTOXS daily rate 0.738 at NH4=82.8mg/L; compounding over 33d gives final biomass ratio
 138.00  2.0                      NH4_TOX_K (mg/L), NH4_TOX_N (Hill coeff)


