*POTAS  Potassium Parameters (optimized for lettuce)
! Potassium concentrations are typically 5-10x higher than phosphorus
! K is highly mobile in plants - luxury uptake is common
! K stress primarily affects stomatal conductance and water use efficiency
!
! Two options for Optimum and minimum K concentrations for shoots:
! (1) supply values for shoots (leaf plus stem)
! (2) supply values individually for leaf and for stem
! If positive values for shoots are supplied, any values supplied for leaf and
! stem will be ignored.
!
! K concentrations in % dry matter (divide by 100 for decimal fraction)
   -99.0   -99.0   -99.0  Optimum Shoot K Conc (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
! 3-stage K% targets (Heinen 1994): transplant 7.5% → peak/stable 9.4% from DAS15 onward
  0.0750  0.0940  0.0940  Optimum Leaf K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.0900  0.0730  0.0560  Optimum Stem K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.0850  0.0850  0.0750  Optimum Root K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
   -99.0  0.0200  0.0150  Optimum Shell K Conc (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
   -99.0  0.0080  0.0060  Optimum Seed K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)

   -99.0   -99.0   -99.0  Minimum Shoot K Conc (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.0100  0.0090  0.0070  Minimum Leaf K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.0100  0.0090  0.0070  Minimum Stem K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.0100  0.0090  0.0070  Minimum Root K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
   -99.0  0.0080  0.0060  Minimum Shell K Conc (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
   -99.0  0.0040  0.0030  Minimum Seed K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)

! Luxury K concentrations (K can be stored above optimum without benefit)
  0.1350  0.1100  0.0860  Luxury Shoot K Conc  (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
  0.1200  0.1200  0.1000  Luxury Root K Conc   (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)

! N:K ratio constraints (vegetative tissue)
    3.00    3.50    4.00  Maximum Veg N:K ratio (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
    0.35    0.35    0.35  Minimum Veg N:K ratio (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)

! P:K ratio constraints (vegetative tissue)
    0.20    0.25    0.30  Maximum Veg P:K ratio (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)
    0.05    0.08    0.10  Minimum Veg P:K ratio (emergence, 1st flower, full seed)

! K stress thresholds (K stress ratio at which stress begins)
    0.50    0.65  SRATPHOTO_K, SRATSTOM - K stress thresholds for photosyn, stomata
    0.20          FracKMobil - max fraction of K which can be mobilized per day (higher than P)
    1.00          FracKUptake - fraction of available soil K used for uptake
    1.00          KMAX_LUXURY - no luxury storage; KTOTDEM=KTotDem only, tracks opt smoothly
